article.headline: Houston 85, East Carolina 67
article.story: HOUSTON -- Aubrey Coleman scored 23 points while Marcus Cousin and Qa'rraan Calhoun each had double-doubles to lead Houston to an 85-67 victory over East Carolina on Wednesday night. Cousin scored 18 points and grabbed 13 rebounds while Calhoun scored 12 points and had 10 rebounds for Houston (12-4, 3-1 Conference USA). Kelvin Lewis scored 16 points and DaShaun Williams had 12 for Houston. Sam Hinnant scored 22 points for the Pirates (9-8, 1-3) while Darrius Morrow scored 12 and Jamar Abrams added 10. Brock Young had 12 assists to go along with eight points in the loss. Houston led 51-31 at the half.
